ent-Z14ClothingHeadHelmetKKKCoat = capirote
    .desc = A medieval Spanish headpiece — a tall, conical pointed hood. Originally made of cardboard, capirotes were used by Spanish flagellants. During the Inquisition, fabric-covered capirotes, together with yellow capes, were used to dress those condemned to death.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14ClothingOuterCoatKKK = KKK robe
    .desc = The white robes of the Ku Klux Klan are long white hooded garments that symbolize the anonymity and unity of the organization's members. These robes are often associated with the racist actions of the KKK, emphasizing their ideology of white supremacy.
    .suffix = Z14
